In December 1996 Miguel held a press conference in Buenos Aires, Argentina, where he announced his desire to record a third Romance album and mentioned the possibility of working with Manzanero and Juan Gabriel. He also expressed an interest in singing in Italian and Portuguese,cite news  title=Va por el tercero newspaper=Reforma url=http://busquedas.gruporeforma.com/reforma/Pages/BuscaImpresa.aspx publisher=Grupo Reforma trans_title=Going for third date= 1996-12-10 language=Spanish accessdate=2011-04-09subscription required although the album's songs are originally all in Spanish. Two months later Manzanero confirmed that he was working with Miguel on another bolero-inspired ballads album, under the tentative title Tercer Romance Third Romance.
cite journal  last = Lannert  first = John  date = 1997-02-08  title = Latin Notas  journal = Billboard  publisher = Nielsen Business Media, Inc.  volume = 109  issue = 6  page = 32  url = http://books.google.com/books?id=wA4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA31&dq=%22luis%20miguel%22%20intitle%3Abillboard&pg=PA32#v=onepage&q&f=false  accessdate = 2011-03-28 Miguel's record label confirmed that fourteen tracks would be included on the album under the title Romances.cite news  title= Es Luis Miguel un clasico del romance first=Anglica  last= De Len newspaper=Reforma url=http://busquedas.gruporeforma.com/reforma/Pages/BuscaImpresa.aspx publisher=Grupo Reforma trans_title=Is Luis Miguel romantic classic date= 1997-07-16 language=Spanish accessdate=2011-03-28subscription required Por Debajo de la Mesa was written by Manzanero as one of the two original compositions for the album along with Contigo Estar Contigo.cite web title=Romances&nbsp; Credits url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/romances-r308222/credits accessdate=2011-02-19 work=Allmusic publisher=Rovi Corporation

