A music video for Por Debajo de la Mesa was filmed in New York City which features Miguel performing at the Rainbow Room with the video being shot in black-and-white.cite video  people = Miguel, Luis performer  title = Por Debajo de la Mesa url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=giAE7Yz7gHI   medium = Television  publisher = Warner Music Warner Music Mexico  location = New York City  date = 1997  The song was included on his greatest hits album Mis Boleros Favoritos 2002 and Grandes xitos Luis Miguel album  Grandes xitos 2005.cite web title=Por Debajo de la Mesa&nbsp; Luis Miguel url=http://www.allmusic.com/song/por-debajo-de-la-mesa-mt0035008714s accessdate=2014-01-03 work=Allmusic publisher=Rovi Corporation A live version of the song was included on his album Vivo Luis Miguel album Vivo 2000 as part of the Romances Medley.cite web title=Vivo&nbsp; Overview url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/vivo-mw0000619848 accessdate=2014-01-03 work=Allmusic publisher=Rovi Corporation

Release and reception
Por Debajo de la Mesa serviced to radio stations across Latin America on July 15, 1997.cite news  title= Llega a todo el mundo 'Por Debajo de la Mesa first=Carlos  last= Meraz url=http://busquedas.gruporeforma.com/reforma/Pages/BuscaImpresa.aspx newspaper= El Norte publisher=Grupo Reforma date= 1997-07-15 accessdate=2011-03-28 language=Spanishsubscription required In the United States, the song debuted at number two on the Hot Latin Songs Billboard Hot Latin Songs chart on the week of August 2, 1997.cite web  title=Top Latin Songs&nbsp; Week of August 7, 1997  work=Billboard  publisher=Prometheus Global Media  date=1997-08-02  url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1997-08-02/latin-songs  accessdate=2011-04-15  Six weeks later, it peaked at number one on the chart where and remained on the position for four weeks.cite web  title=Top Latin Songs&nbsp; Week of September 6, 1997  work=Billboard  publisher=Prometheus Global Media  date=1997-09-07   url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1997-09-06/latin-songs  accessdate=2009-04-15  Por Debajo de la Mesa ended 1997 as the eighth best-performing Latin single of the year in the United States. The track also peaked at number one on the Latin Pop Songs Billboard Latin Pop Songs chart where it spent five weeks on top of the chart and was the best-performing Latin pop song of the year in the country.cite web  title= Latin Pop Songs&nbsp; Week of August 30, 1997  work=Billboard  publisher=Prometheus Global Media  date=1997-08-30 url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/1997-08-30/latin-pop-songs  accessdate=2014-01-01

Despite giving Romances a positive review, Chicago Tribune editor Achy Obejas called Por Debajo de la Mesa a lame song and cited it as one of the songs where Miguel beginning is to slip on his ballad recordings.cite web  last =  Obejas  first = Achy  date = 1997-10-03 title= Music. Album Reviews  Luis Miguel Romances url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1997-10-03/entertainment/9710030393_1_armando-manzanero-songs-oldies work=Chicago Tribune accessdate=2011-02-19 It received a nomination for Lo Nuestro Award for Pop Song of the Year Pop Song of the Year at the Premio Lo Nuestro 1998 Lo Nuestro Awards of 1998, losing to Si Tu Supieras by Alejandro Fernndez.cite news url=http://wvw.nacion.com/viva/1998/abril/03/espec9.html title=Premios Lo Nuestro: Los galardones a la msica latina sern entregados en mayo prximo  last=Barquero first=Christopher language=Spanish work=La Nacin San Jos La Nacin publisher=Grupo Nacin GN, S.A. year=1998 accessdate=2013-06-14cite web  url=http://archivo.univision.com/content/content.jhtml?cid=490998 title=Lo Nuestro 1998  Historia  language=Spanish  work=Univision  publisher=Univision Communications, Inc  accessdate=2013-06-14  year=1998 Manzanero was given a Broadcast Music, Inc. BMI Latin Award for composition of the song due to it being one of the best-performing Latin songs of the year.cite web title=BMI Latin Awards: 1999 url=http://www.bmi.com/news/entry/533568 date=1999-01-01 publisher=Broadcast Music, Inc. accessdate=2011-02-19

